Package de.parsemis.miner.filter

Contains post-search fragment filter.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
FragmentFilter<NodeType,EdgeType> This interface encapsulates the capability to filter fragments after the search
 

Class Summary
ClosedFilter<NodeType,EdgeType> This class provide a post-filter to filter out non-closed fragments
GraphShrinkingFilter<NodeType,EdgeType> This class weights all storable nodes by (count-1)*(size-1) [as SubDue] where count represents number of embeddings and size is the sum of nodes and edges it finally returns just the n best weighted fragments
SingleRootedFilter<NodeType,EdgeType> This class provide a post filter to filter out single rooted fragments.
ZaretskyFilter<NodeType,EdgeType> This class provide a post-filter to filter out single sinked fragments as used by Zaretsky.
 

Package de.parsemis.miner.filter Description

Contains post-search fragment filter.

To achive compareable results as other mining algorithms a filtering of the found fragment set after a mining run might be necessary. Removing unwanted fragments during the search is most times more efficient, but only possible if you can decide on the basis of the fragment and its direct children if it is relevant.

Author:
Marc Woerlein (woerlein@informatik.uni-erlangen.de)
